\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Correlations of observable galaxy properties with $\mathrm  {VfResid}$. The dark halo amplitude ($\mathrm  {haloK}$, $r = +0.60$) is the strongest predictor, followed by the MOND improvement metric ($r = -0.54$). Pure structural properties (not shown) fail entirely to predict $\mathrm  {VfResid}$ ($\mathrm  {LOO}\tmspace  +\thickmuskip {.2777em}R^2 < 0$), confirming that $\mathrm  {VfResid}$ carries genuine halo information beyond baryonic structure.}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:vfresid}{{1}{2}{Correlations of observable galaxy properties with $\vfresid $. The dark halo amplitude ($\haloK $, $r = +0.60$) is the strongest predictor, followed by the MOND improvement metric ($r = -0.54$). Pure structural properties (not shown) fail entirely to predict $\vfresid $ ($\loo \;R^2 < 0$), confirming that $\vfresid $ carries genuine halo information beyond baryonic structure}{figure.1}{}}
