\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Regime dependence of the $\mathrm  {VfResid}$--$a_0$ coupling. Correlation strength $r(\mathrm  {VfResid}, \qopname  \relax o{log}a_0)$ is plotted as a function of the minimum $V_{\rm  flat}$ threshold applied to the sample. The coupling strengthens monotonically from $r \sim 0.70$ (all galaxies) to $r \sim 0.83$ (above 180\nobreakspace  {}${\rm  km\,s^{-1}}$), with a marked transition near 120\nobreakspace  {}${\rm  km\,s^{-1}}$ (dashed line).}}{3}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:regime}{{3}{3}{Regime dependence of the $\vfresid $--$\azero $ coupling. Correlation strength $r(\vfresid , \log \azero )$ is plotted as a function of the minimum $\vflat $ threshold applied to the sample. The coupling strengthens monotonically from $r \sim 0.70$ (all galaxies) to $r \sim 0.83$ (above 180~$\kms $), with a marked transition near 120~$\kms $ (dashed line)}{figure.3}{}}
