\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces External validation using frozen training coefficients. Gold bars show the Core-only transfer gap (with improved $M_{\rm  host}$ estimation); blue bars show Core$+\mathrm  {VfResid}$. The Core alone fails in the full sample and very-high-$V_{\rm  flat}$ regime, while $\mathrm  {VfResid}$ provides the dominant transferable signal in every subsample. The strongest performance (59.0 per cent) is achieved for Q$=1$ galaxies with $V_{\rm  flat}\geq 120\nobreakspace  {}{\rm  km\,s^{-1}}$.}}{4}{figure.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:external}{{4}{4}{External validation using frozen training coefficients. Gold bars show the Core-only transfer gap (with improved $\mhost $ estimation); blue bars show Core$+\vfresid $. The Core alone fails in the full sample and very-high-$\vflat $ regime, while $\vfresid $ provides the dominant transferable signal in every subsample. The strongest performance (59.0 per cent) is achieved for Q$=1$ galaxies with $\vflat \geq 120~\kms $}{figure.4}{}}
