\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Physical interpretation: evidence scores for four candidate hypotheses. H4 (dynamical integration) leads with score\nobreakspace  {}10, driven by regime-strengthening of dynamical coherence ($\qopname  \relax o{log}$MR: $r = 0.11 \to 0.51$ from low to high $V_{\rm  flat}$). H1 and H3 tie at score\nobreakspace  {}7; H2 is weakest. The key discriminant is that H4 proxies \emph  {strengthen} with $V_{\rm  flat}$ while feedback proxies \emph  {fade} --- matching the activation pattern of the coupling law itself.}}{5}{figure.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:hypothesis}{{5}{5}{Physical interpretation: evidence scores for four candidate hypotheses. H4 (dynamical integration) leads with score~10, driven by regime-strengthening of dynamical coherence ($\log $MR: $r = 0.11 \to 0.51$ from low to high $\vflat $). H1 and H3 tie at score~7; H2 is weakest. The key discriminant is that H4 proxies \emph {strengthen} with $\vflat $ while feedback proxies \emph {fade} --- matching the activation pattern of the coupling law itself}{figure.5}{}}
