\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Synthesis: the hierarchical coupling law. The structural core sets the $a_0$ baseline; the $\mathrm  {VfResid}$ channel carries the dominant halo coupling signal (36--69 per cent irreducible, mediating all halo proxies); the $\mathrm  {lhOuter}$ channel adds secondary outer-halo information; and a $V_{\rm  flat}$-dependent regime gate controls activation. The best-supported physical interpretation is dynamical integration (H4, score\nobreakspace  {}10).}}{5}{figure.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:synthesis}{{6}{5}{Synthesis: the hierarchical coupling law. The structural core sets the $\azero $ baseline; the $\vfresid $ channel carries the dominant halo coupling signal (36--69 per cent irreducible, mediating all halo proxies); the $\lhOuter $ channel adds secondary outer-halo information; and a $\vflat $-dependent regime gate controls activation. The best-supported physical interpretation is dynamical integration (H4, score~10)}{figure.6}{}}
